a shock to the heart.

522
00:19:07.354 --> 00:19:09.063
Family?
- Yeah. husband's en route.

523
00:19:09.064 --> 00:19:10.857
Leave the defib pads on
and take her up in a minute.

524
00:19:10.858 --> 00:19:12.233
I'm gonna chaperone
a nerve block real quick.

525
00:19:12.234 --> 00:19:13.318
Go.

526
00:19:15.320 --> 00:19:16.946
Where's Dr. Al-Hashimi?

527
00:19:16.947 --> 00:19:18.907
She was just here.

528
00:19:28.292 --> 00:19:30.418
- Hello. everyone.
I'm Dr. Shen.

529
00:19:30.419 --> 00:19:32.253
Heard a rumor someone
needed a nerve block.

530
00:19:32.254 --> 00:19:33.921
I'm guessing that's you.

531
00:19:33.922 --> 00:19:36.007
Probably so. although.

532
00:19:36.008 --> 00:19:37.592
you know.
I don't have much pain.

533
00:19:37.593 --> 00:19:39.677
I guess it's my diabetes.

534
00:19:39.678 --> 00:19:43.222
We still need to numb you up
to do a proper deep clean.

535
00:19:43.223 --> 00:19:45.099
You guys do
whatever you gotta do.

536
00:19:45.100 --> 00:19:47.602
Three shots. median.
ulnar. and radial.

537
00:19:47.603 --> 00:19:49.437
2 grams of Ancef.
100 milligrams of Gent

538
00:19:49.438 --> 00:19:50.688
for gram-negative coverage.

539
00:19:50.689 --> 00:19:52.064
How'd you do this?

540
00:19:52.065 --> 00:19:54.734
Oh. a family reunion tug-of-war.

541
00:19:54.735 --> 00:19:56.903
I wrapped the rope around
my hand for better grip.

542
00:19:56.904 --> 00:19:59.947
And when we fell down. those
bastards just kept pulling.

543
00:19:59.948 --> 00:20:01.449
Dirty.

544
00:20:01.450 --> 00:20:03.951
- Nah. it's just...
just the way we play.

545
00:20:06.789 --> 00:20:08.289
Michael. you got a second?

546
00:20:08.290 --> 00:20:09.916
Uh. not really. no.

547
00:20:09.917 --> 00:20:11.667
Well. how about
showing me a little respect

548
00:20:11.668 --> 00:20:13.836
and finding one?

549
00:20:13.837 --> 00:20:14.962
Sorry. Caleb.

550
00:20:14.963 --> 00:20:16.464
Are you feeling disrespected?

551
00:20:16.465 --> 00:20:18.466
Given that you've been
actively blowing me off

552
00:20:18.467 --> 00:20:20.134
all day. yeah.
maybe a little bit.

553
00:20:20.135 --> 00:20:21.595
But I have a thick skin.

554
00:20:22.888 --> 00:20:24.472
What can I do for you?

555
00:20:24.473 --> 00:20:27.350
"Should have found
a higher place to jump from."

556
00:20:27.351 --> 00:20:29.770
It's an interesting diagnosis.
Doctor.

557
00:20:33.690 --> 00:20:35.316
No pithy retort?

558
00:20:35.317 --> 00:20:37.401
Yeah. I didn't think so.

559
00:20:37.402 --> 00:20:39.654
Uh. I just came to say goodbye.

560
00:20:39.655 --> 00:20:41.405
I'm leaving soon.

561
00:20:41.406 --> 00:20:43.200
I know you are too.

562
00:20:44.535 --> 00:20:46.203
Yes.

563
00:20:47.496 --> 00:20:49.747
Keep my number handy.
just in case. huh?

564
00:20:49.748 --> 00:20:51.749
Yes. I promise I will.

565
00:20:51.750 --> 00:20:53.085
Thank you. Caleb.

566
00:20:55.546 --> 00:20:57.755
We're gonna give you one
Diflucan pill to take home.

567
00:20:57.756 --> 00:21:00.633
Take it in three days
if your symptoms persist.

568
00:21:00.634 --> 00:21:02.385
How do I get there?

569
00:21:02.386 --> 00:21:03.845
Where's that?

570
00:21:03.846 --> 00:21:05.513
Home.

571
00:21:05.514 --> 00:21:06.806
Do you know where you live?

572
00:21:06.807 --> 00:21:08.683
Of course I do. It's not far.

573
00:21:08.684 --> 00:21:11.144
But I don't have
a way to get there.

574
00:21:12.312 --> 00:21:13.896
How'd you get here?

575
00:21:13.897 --> 00:21:16.232
My... my neighbor Gwen
dropped me off.

576
00:21:16.233 --> 00:21:18.568
but she can't drive at night.

577
00:21:18.569 --> 00:21:21.320
We could call you
an Uber or a taxi.

578
00:21:21.321 --> 00:21:23.990
I don't have any money.

579
00:21:23.991 --> 00:21:25.658
Excuse me.

580
00:21:25.659 --> 00:21:27.201
Can I help?

581
00:21:27.202 --> 00:21:28.911
Mrs. Clymer has
been discharged.

582
00:21:28.912 --> 00:21:29.954
but has no way home.

583
00:21:29.955 --> 00:21:30.997
I'm so sorry.

584
00:21:30.998 --> 00:21:31.998
I don't mean to be a burden.

585
00:21:31.999 --> 00:21:33.374
No burden at all.

586
00:21:33.375 --> 00:21:36.294
Why don't we call you a Lyft?

587
00:21:36.295 --> 00:21:37.628
What is that?

588
00:21:37.629 --> 00:21:38.963
It's like a taxi service.

589
00:21:38.964 --> 00:21:40.798
If you put your address in here.

590
00:21:40.799 --> 00:21:43.217
a car will arrive in a few
minutes to bring you home.

591
00:21:43.218 --> 00:21:44.510
- Oh.
- My treat.

592
00:21:45.721 --> 00:21:49.849
That's very kind of you. truly.

593
00:21:49.850 --> 00:21:51.392
Perfect.

594
00:21:51.393 --> 00:21:53.477
OK. Olive. could you take
Mrs. Clymer out

595
00:21:53.478 --> 00:21:56.188
to the ambulance bay.
where Florian will be

596
00:21:56.189 --> 00:21:58.357
arriving in six minutes
in a white Toyota Camry?

597
00:21:58.358 --> 00:21:59.567
You bet.

598
00:21:59.568 --> 00:22:00.902
Thank you.

599
00:22:00.903 --> 00:22:03.070
I could use some good karma.

600
00:22:03.071 --> 00:22:04.865
OK.

601
00:22:07.659 --> 00:22:09.912
Oh. uh. hey.

602
00:22:11.455 --> 00:22:12.747
Relax. buddy.

603
00:22:12.748 --> 00:22:14.582
It's Advil.

604
00:22:14.583 --> 00:22:16.918
No. I didn't think you were...

605
00:22:18.253 --> 00:22:19.962
Headache?

606
00:22:19.963 --> 00:22:23.049
Uh. I tweaked my back a little

607
00:22:23.050 --> 00:22:25.885
lifting that overheated kid.

608
00:22:25.886 --> 00:22:27.219
I guess I should get used to

609
00:22:27.220 --> 00:22:29.931
playing through the pain
again. huh?

610
00:22:29.932 --> 00:22:32.433
You look like you got into
shape since I saw you last.

611
00:22:32.434 --> 00:22:34.393
Didn't peg you as a gym guy.

612
00:22:34.394 --> 00:22:35.770
Oh. no.

613
00:22:35.771 --> 00:22:38.606
I'm maybe more of a barn guy.

614
00:22:38.607 --> 00:22:41.652
I'm helping out a friend
on the farm. so...

615
00:22:43.320 --> 00:22:44.362
Nice.

616
00:22:44.363 --> 00:22:46.072
I'm picturing "Babe."

617
00:22:46.073 --> 00:22:47.865
except instead of
Farmer Hoggett. it's you.

618
00:22:47.866 --> 00:22:49.241
And instead of a pig...

619
00:22:49.242 --> 00:22:51.161
Can you cut the shit?

620
00:22:52.704 --> 00:22:54.038
Excuse me?

621
00:22:54.039 --> 00:22:56.290
The sarcasm thing.
the... the... the...

622
00:22:56.291 --> 00:22:58.042
the little buddy routine.
like... like... like.

623
00:22:58.043 --> 00:22:59.919
you're what. you're
the Skipper. I'm Gilligan?

624
00:22:59.920 --> 00:23:01.796
Dude. you're not the Skipper.

625
00:23:01.797 --> 00:23:04.090
- I know I'm not the Skipper.
Robby is the Skipper.

626
00:23:04.091 --> 00:23:06.175
- No. Robby is the Professor.
Dana's the Skipper.

627
00:23:06.176 --> 00:23:07.760
OK. somebody's watched
a lot of Nick at Nite.

628
00:23:07.761 --> 00:23:10.137
So who am I?

629
00:23:10.138 --> 00:23:12.306
Play whatever part you like.

630
00:23:12.307 --> 00:23:14.685
Just don't pick mine for me.

631
00:23:16.186 --> 00:23:17.478
OK.

632
00:23:17.479 --> 00:23:19.522
OK. that's fair.

633
00:23:19.523 --> 00:23:21.190
You got it.

634
00:23:21.191 --> 00:23:23.442
Thank you.

635
00:23:23.443 --> 00:23:25.820
You headed home?

636
00:23:25.821 --> 00:23:28.614
Uh. no. I'm waiting on Robby.

637
00:23:28.615 --> 00:23:30.366
He asked me to house-sit
while he's gone.

638
00:23:30.367 --> 00:23:33.245
So I'm waiting for the keys.
the alarm code.

639
00:23:34.663 --> 00:23:35.997
Nice. Nice.

640
00:23:35.998 --> 00:23:37.832
Yeah. I've...
I've seen his place.

641
00:23:37.833 --> 00:23:40.167
You're in for a sweet setup.

642
00:23:40.168 --> 00:23:42.253
Cool.

643
00:23:42.254 --> 00:23:46.090
I'm sorry if I came across
a little strong.

644
00:23:46.091 --> 00:23:48.426
Don't apologize
for standing up for yourself.

645
00:23:48.427 --> 00:23:50.428
It's a healthy habit.

646
00:23:52.347 --> 00:23:54.265
You know. I really don't
need to see this again.

647
00:23:54.266 --> 00:23:55.766
No. this is my favorite part.

648
00:23:57.310 --> 00:23:58.352
My hand's starting to cramp.

649
00:23:58.353 --> 00:23:59.603
We gotta be done soon.

650
00:23:59.604 --> 00:24:01.355
Oh. you can be done now.

651
00:24:01.356 --> 00:24:04.443
But if you want to the hospital
to cover you. last one.

652
00:24:10.073 --> 00:24:13.075
- Hey. Robby.
It was an accident. man.

653
00:24:13.076 --> 00:24:14.660
What are you talking about?

654
00:24:14.661 --> 00:24:16.830
Your bike.

655
00:24:24.671 --> 00:24:27.173
Son of a bitch.

656
00:24:27.174 --> 00:24:29.968
Oh. motherfucker!

657
00:24:31.428 --> 00:24:33.387
Robby. GSW to the head.

658
00:24:33.388 --> 00:24:34.722
Somebody hit my bike.

659
00:24:34.723 --> 00:24:36.265
Dude. that sucks.

660
00:24:36.266 --> 00:24:37.808
Is it still rideable?

661
00:24:39.061 --> 00:24:40.686
It better be.

662
00:24:40.687 --> 00:24:42.897
Elbridge Gerry. 25.
stable with good vitals.

663
00:24:42.898 --> 00:24:44.523
♪ Of thee I sing ♪

664
00:24:44.524 --> 00:24:46.067
Was shooting his
22 caliber pistol in the air

665
00:24:46.068 --> 00:24:47.568
with an aluminum pot
on his head for protection.

666
00:24:47.569 --> 00:24:48.903
Didn't work.

667
00:24:48.904 --> 00:24:50.321
He's had about a quart
of Seagrams 7

668
00:24:50.322 --> 00:24:51.572
and will probably light up
a tox screen

669
00:24:51.573 --> 00:24:53.908
like a Roman candle.

670
00:24:53.909 --> 00:24:56.535
♪ We start fucking ♪

671
00:24:56.536 --> 00:24:57.995
Real wordsmith.

672
00:24:57.996 --> 00:24:59.413
Entry wound
in the frontal scalp.

673
00:24:59.414 --> 00:25:00.748
seems to have tracked down
the forehead.

674
00:25:00.749 --> 00:25:01.874
As alert and oriented
as you can be

675
00:25:01.875 --> 00:25:03.084
after multiple bong hits.

676
00:25:03.085 --> 00:25:04.585
Got vital satting 98
on room air.

677
00:25:04.586 --> 00:25:05.920
- Sorry. Robby.
- Don't you fucking leave.

678
00:25:05.921 --> 00:25:06.921
- I can explain.
- I will be right back.

679
00:25:06.922 --> 00:25:07.922
What's this?

680
00:25:07.923 --> 00:25:09.381
Trauma 2.

681
00:25:09.382 --> 00:25:10.758
Low velocity GSW to the head.

682
00:25:10.759 --> 00:25:12.218
seems to have
remained extracranial.

683
00:25:12.219 --> 00:25:13.761
Lucky guy.

684
00:25:13.762 --> 00:25:17.932
♪ Gloria. Gloria.
here's a dollar! ♪

685
00:25:17.933 --> 00:25:20.434
After a fireworks
explosion resulting

686
00:25:20.435 --> 00:25:22.812
in the loss of two fingers.

687
00:25:22.813 --> 00:25:24.980
Ooh. that sounds nasty.

688
00:25:24.981 --> 00:25:27.650
Yeah. that was a sad one.

689
00:25:27.651 --> 00:25:29.068
Parents were deported.

690
00:25:29.069 --> 00:25:31.445
Big sister works a full-time job

691
00:25:31.446 --> 00:25:32.988
and is the sole caregiver.

692
00:25:32.989 --> 00:25:34.657
Been there. done that.

693
00:25:34.658 --> 00:25:36.450
Your parents were deported?

694
00:25:36.451 --> 00:25:38.328
- Oh. no.
I thought she said departed.

695
00:25:39.955 --> 00:25:41.747
Did either of you guys work on

696
00:25:41.748 --> 00:25:44.583
the Revolutionary War
reenactors earlier?

697
00:25:44.584 --> 00:25:47.294
Why. you didn't think you
could pull off a tricorn hat?

698
00:25:47.295 --> 00:25:50.131
Maybe.

699
00:25:50.132 --> 00:25:51.799
I've always loved history.

700
00:25:51.800 --> 00:25:55.803
and Colonial Williamsburg
was my favorite school trip.

701
00:25:55.804 --> 00:25:57.471
And. you know.
there's always the Ren Faire.

702
00:25:57.472 --> 00:25:59.932
but that's just once a year.

703
00:25:59.933 --> 00:26:02.269
How often do you think
the reenactors get together?

704
00:26:03.895 --> 00:26:05.646
I don't know. No.

705
00:26:05.647 --> 00:26:07.481
You should definitely
look into that.

706
00:26:07.482 --> 00:26:08.774
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

707
00:26:08.775 --> 00:26:10.068
OK.

708
00:26:20.036 --> 00:26:22.163
Deep-throated husky
with a touch of bitch.

709
00:26:22.164 --> 00:26:23.664
That's her tune.

710
00:26:23.665 --> 00:26:24.999
That's what I thought.
but you're the expert.

711
00:26:25.000 --> 00:26:26.626
I just needed to make sure.

712
00:26:28.044 --> 00:26:29.795
I was going through
Billings once.

713
00:26:29.796 --> 00:26:33.340
Cop saw my colors. jacked me up.

714
00:26:33.341 --> 00:26:34.800
kept me overnight.

715
00:26:34.801 --> 00:26:38.470
They threw my sweetheart
in the impound yard.

716
00:26:38.471 --> 00:26:40.347
They claimed
someone backed into it.

717
00:26:40.348 --> 00:26:43.517
but you could see where they
took their hammer to it. man.

718
00:26:43.518 --> 00:26:45.019
You gotta be careful out there.

719
00:26:45.020 --> 00:26:46.353
This is all pretty minor.
though. right?

720
00:26:46.354 --> 00:26:48.647
Yeah. shit.
this is just cosmetic.

721
00:26:48.648 --> 00:26:51.150
Bring it in tomorrow.
and we'll get Bonnie right.

722
00:26:51.151 --> 00:26:52.860
- Well. this will bend back.
This will tighten up.

723
00:26:52.861 --> 00:26:54.528
I can do all that myself.
- Jesus. let me do it.

724
00:26:54.529 --> 00:26:55.821
There's no charge.
- What?

725
00:26:55.822 --> 00:26:57.198
You don't owe me anything.
except

726
00:26:57.199 --> 00:26:59.700
take care of yourself
while I'm gone.

727
00:26:59.701 --> 00:27:01.535
Boy. this record
never stops. huh?

728
00:27:01.536 --> 00:27:04.455
Nah. it's dance till you drop!

729
00:27:04.456 --> 00:27:05.956
Then what?

730
00:27:05.957 --> 00:27:08.042
Teach the kids the steps
before you do.

731
00:27:08.043 --> 00:27:09.376
And then what?

732
00:27:09.377 --> 00:27:10.878
Hope they make it
farther than you.

733
00:27:10.879 --> 00:27:12.546
Hey. Robby.
you're coming or going?

734
00:27:12.547 --> 00:27:14.340
- I'm going. pretty soon.
What have you got here?

735
00:27:14.341 --> 00:27:17.218
Lyman Paine. 53. single MVC.

736
00:27:17.219 --> 00:27:18.385
Drove into a telephone pole.

737
00:27:18.386 --> 00:27:19.720
Passenger space intrusion?

738
00:27:19.721 --> 00:27:20.846
No. head on.

739
00:27:20.847 --> 00:27:21.847
Intoxicated?

740
00:27:21.848 --> 00:27:23.766
No ETOH on his breath.

741
00:27:23.767 --> 00:27:25.559
Either syncope. seizure.

742
00:27:25.560 --> 00:27:28.062
or he just fell asleep
at the wheel.

743
00:27:28.063 --> 00:27:30.105
Airbag deployed.
unconscious at the scene.

744
00:27:30.106 --> 00:27:31.106
but he's waking up.

745
00:27:31.107 --> 00:27:32.608
BP 140 over 80.

746
00:27:32.609 --> 00:27:34.401
pulse 120. pulse ox 98.

747
00:27:34.402 --> 00:27:35.694
no obvious injuries.

748
00:27:35.695 --> 00:27:36.695
Why don't you guys head on in?

749
00:27:36.696 --> 00:27:37.906
I'll meet you in a minute.

750
00:27:42.661 --> 00:27:45.412
Well. hey. buddy.
I guess this is it.

751
00:27:45.413 --> 00:27:47.248
Make those appointments
next week. you know?

752
00:27:47.249 --> 00:27:49.416
I'll call you from the road
to make sure you do.

753
00:27:49.417 --> 00:27:51.085
- Don't do that. man.
- What?

754
00:27:51.086 --> 00:27:53.045
Don't shine me on.

755
00:27:53.046 --> 00:27:55.005
I'm not.

756
00:27:55.006 --> 00:27:56.423
Jesus.

757
00:27:56.424 --> 00:27:58.259
I get it.

758
00:27:58.260 --> 00:28:01.304
Hard place to leave.
a harder place to stay.

759
00:28:02.931 --> 00:28:04.140
Yeah.

760
00:28:06.476 --> 00:28:09.228
Look. I'm not ready
to say goodbye yet.

761
00:28:09.229 --> 00:28:12.731
So go do what you gotta do.
and I'll get some tools

762
00:28:12.732 --> 00:28:15.109
from the truck
and see if I can't make

763
00:28:15.110 --> 00:28:17.320
Bonnie smile again for you.

764
00:28:20.991 --> 00:28:22.241
OK.

765
00:28:22.242 --> 00:28:23.910
OK. then.

766
00:28:30.917 --> 00:28:33.294
- Robby. man. I'm so sorry.
We've been on for 14 straight.

767
00:28:33.295 --> 00:28:34.920
I thought I cleared it.
- It's all right.

768
00:28:34.921 --> 00:28:36.171
Honestly. I feel terrible.

769
00:28:36.172 --> 00:28:38.007
No real harm done.

770
00:28:38.008 --> 00:28:39.800
I was bound to nick it up
on the road anyway.

771
00:28:39.801 --> 00:28:43.137
First blood drawn.
it's a good omen really.

772
00:28:43.138 --> 00:28:44.596
Thought he'd be more pissed.

773
00:28:44.597 --> 00:28:46.640
I thought you might get punched.

774
00:28:46.641 --> 00:28:48.142
Chest and belly look good.

775
00:28:48.143 --> 00:28:49.476
Let me drag Neurosurgery
down here to deal with

776
00:28:49.477 --> 00:28:50.644
the C-spine before I go.

777
00:28:50.645 --> 00:28:53.147
- You off?
- Yep. an hour ago.

778
00:28:53.148 --> 00:28:55.107
Can't you tell?
- How you doing. sir?

779
00:28:55.108 --> 00:28:57.818
Actually. not too good.

780
00:28:57.819 --> 00:28:59.153
The tingling is getting worse.

781
00:28:59.154 --> 00:29:00.821
It's in both my arms now.

782
00:29:00.822 --> 00:29:02.448
I feel like something's wrong.

783
00:29:02.449 --> 00:29:04.658
- Hey. man.
